main event: Two objects resembling stars were observed in Burbank, California, on 13 February 1957.
interesting points: The objects were seen at high altitude and exhibited red and green flashing lights., One object appeared as a red light while the second faded out., The sighting lasted for 5 minutes., The area is known for heavy air traffic due to its proximity to Lockheed Air Terminal., The conclusion by observers was that it was probably aircraft.
sighted object: two objects resembling stars with flashing lights
